<br>
Now, I can use the sustem fine in full screen mode, I can even toggle between modes with the f10 key and have no video incompatabilities. When I click on the Persona button, however, all my text goes to a gray on gray format. I cannot read my text box, exp/life/mana bars, etc. I have to completely go down the the desktop and restart.<br>
<br>
I have installed the newest version of the video driver and run all DirectX 8.1 diagnostics. Everything checks out ok.  Any ideas?<br>
<br>
Alternatively, how do I get to the new alternative persona screen without looting anything? If I could bypass the traditional persona screen I could most likely aviod the problem.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Borm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufalzure.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falzure</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/6/02 9:02:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=248.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Video Question</span><hr size=1> I assume you mean the Rage Mobolity 128 (thats its model number, not how much memory it has <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), and you have 256MB of system memory?<br>
<br>
This should work just fine, there are a few things you are going to want to change.<br>
<br>
First off goto the options section when you first start EQ and in the &quot;Luclin Engine Settings&quot; (this is the same regardless of whether you have Luclin or not),<br>
<br>
Make sure the following are un-ticked (in other words, empty)<br>
Textture Compression<br>
Mip Mapping<br>
<br>
Make sure the following are ticked (in other words, check marked)<br>
Texture Caching<br>
<br>
Next change the Resolution to 800x600 and texture quality to low.  I would also suggest turning off all Luclin models if you have Lucling, or turning off Velious textures if you have Velius and not Luclin.<br>
<br>
Click OK and load up the game.<br>
<br>
Once you are in game goto your display options and make sure SCREENS SAME RESOLUTION is ON.  Now F10 back into your full screen mode, and you will be able to access the new windows (press I for the new persona window, V for alternate advancement, ect.)<br>
<br>
Be forwarned that there are still some situations where the &quot;old style&quot; windows will be used, such as the bank and trade windows.  Hopefully these changes will get rid of the garbled text problems your having.<br>
<br>
If not try scalling down more graphics options such as turning the clip plane down to minnium, turn 3d sky off, level of detail off ect.  If none of that helps, it may just be an incompatibility with the video card.<br>
<br>
